.TH "notifier_call_chain" 9 "notifier_call_chain" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
notifier_call_chain \- Informs the registered notifiers about an event.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" notifier_call_chain
.BI "(struct notifier_block **nl "  ","
.BI "unsigned long val "  ","
.BI "void *v "  ","
.BI "int nr_to_call "  ","
.BI "int *nr_calls "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nl" 12
Pointer to head of the blocking notifier chain
.IP "val" 12
Value passed unmodified to notifier function
.IP "v" 12
Pointer passed unmodified to notifier function
.IP "nr_to_call" 12
Number of notifier functions to be called. Don't care
value of this parameter is -1.
.IP "nr_calls" 12
Records the number of notifications sent. Don't care
value of this field is NULL.
